    "It also shows the set of input (left) and readout (right) nodes selected for the analysis 35.",
    "The third panel displays the simulated reservoir's dynamics; the top plot shows the time series of the input signals and the bottom plot shows the simultaneous activation states of the readout nodes within the reservoir (results shown here correspond to the simulated reservoir states with hyperbolic tangent as activation function).",
    "The fourth panel illustrates the learning process that takes place in the readout module during training.",
    "At every time step, the top plot shows the input signals, the middle plot shows the decision function of the classifier ---in the readout module ---, and the bottom plot shows the predicted versus the target signal.",
    "Finally, the fifth panel shows the performance curves as a function of both local (hyperbolic tangent in pink and sigmoid in green) and global (varying the spectral radius α of the connectivity matrix) network dynamics."
